args:
On the plains to the north of Grams, the party meets
a woman named Sheila who knows the way to
the Faerie Kingdom. The prince redoubles his
resolve to head there in order to find out who he
truly is, then crosses over into the forest of the
faeries.
How could you have let them slip away?!
Forgive me, Your Holiness. We brought\nthe might of the Templars to bear on them,\nbut the royal guard and Watch interfered.

So you were denied by the king's lackeys
and a flock of the destitute? Do you seek
to sully my name, or is that simply an
unfortunate accident?
I've no excuses, Your Holiness, but trust\nwe will take appropriate measures to deal\nwith both the royal guard and the Watch.
Crush ANY who dare oppose me!\nAs you continue to leave them unchecked,\nso they continue to test their limits!
Do the same with the Templar captain.\nMy church has no place for ineptitude.
And if you continue to make foolish\nmistakes, Cardinal, you will find your\nplace here to be in equal peril.
I beg your clemency and shall endeavor\nthat nothing of the sort happen again.
I will catch you, pactbearer...and when I\ndo, I will see you kneel before me.

Mete out suitable punishment to the
Watch. As for the king, lodge a protest via
letter. Be certain you don't take things
too far.
And how ought I to deal with the captain?
Send him out to one of the provincial\nparishes for a while. Once the heat has\ndied down, restore him to his post.

Oh, and do keep an eye on Basel and the
apostles. It would pose problems indeed
if they were to turn up in the midst of all
this.

If the seventh and third scions remain in
northern Grastaea, it keeps Alberia's
power divided. A convenient set of
circumstances for us.
And now, I think it is time to issue\nnew orders to Harle...
No need to fret. She's with us.
Sorry about the late arrival. Things in\nGrams took longer than expected.
Allow me to introduce you to Sheila.\nShe will be your guide to the forest of\nthe faeries.
A friend of Gatov's, is it? Well, it looks as\nthough you'll be assisting us quite a bit.\nIt's very nice to meet you.
Er, did I do something wrong?

However, she understands speech perfectly
well. The communication style can take a
little getting used to, but she definitely
knows how to get a job done.
Got it. Sorry about that, Sheila.
And I would ask you once more: Is it your\nwill to go to the Faerie Kingdom, or no?
I'm a bit scared, to be honest.
But I want to know.\nWhat happened to me when I was young?\nAnd who am I REALLY?
No matter what the truth may be,\nI'm going to accept the outcome.
So yes, Gatov. Please take me\nto the Faerie Kingdom.
I can sense the strength of your resolve,\n{player_name}.
I will get you to the Faerie Kingdom even\nat the cost of my own life. This I swear\non the honor of my fallen friend.
Okay, that's all settled. Now where the\nhell is this forest of the faeries everyone's\ntalkin' about?
Okay, I know I haven't had my eyes\nchecked recently or whatever, but I'm\npreeetty sure that's just a big field.
Sheila? If you'd be so kind?
It appeared right before our eyes...
Is that some kind of faerie power, too?
It is indeed. The very existence of the\nforest has been most ingeniously hidden.
Eee hee hee! It looks like things are\nfinally getting interesting.
From this point forward, we will be in the\nfaeries' dominion. Anything can happen\nhere, so be sure to remain vigilant.
